For not a few were convicted because, by being unwilling to have <persName id="#cato">Cato</persName> for one of <persName id="#their_judices">their judices</persName>, they were considered to show that they had no confidence in the justice of their cause; and <persName id="#their_revilers">their revilers</persName> even charged it upon some as matter of great reproach that they would not have <persName id="#cato">Cato</persName> as one of <persName id="#their_judices">their judices</persName> when he was proposed.
XLIX.
