LII.
But when Ariminum was captured, and news came that <persName id="#caesar">Caesar</persName> with <persName id="#his_army">his army</persName> was advancing against the city, then indeed <persName id="#all_men">all men</persName> turned their eyes on <persName id="#cato">Cato</persName>, <persName id="#both_the_people">both the people</persName> and <persName id="#pompeius">Pompeius</persName>, as <persName id="#the_only_man">the only man</persName> who from the first had foreseen and who had first clearly shown the designs of <persName id="#caesar">Caesar</persName>.
