LV.
When <persName id="#pompeius">Pompeius</persName> in order to pursue <persName id="#caesar">Caesar</persName> broke up his camp to march into <personGrp id="#thessaly">Thessaly</personGrp>, he left at <persName id="#dyrrachium">Dyrrachium</persName> a great quantity of arms and stores, and <persName id="#many_kinsmen">many kinsmen</persName> and <persName id="#friends">friends</persName>, and he appointed <persName id="#cato_commander">Cato commander</persName> and <persName id="#guardian">guardian</persName> over <persName id="#all_with_fifteen_cohorts">all with fifteen cohorts</persName>, both because he trusted and feared <persName id="#the_man">the man</persName>.
