Having spent the winter in <personGrp id="#libya">Libya</personGrp> he led forth <persName id="#his_army">his army</persName>; and <persName id="#the_men">the men</persName> were near ten thousand.
LVII.
Matters were in bad plight between <personGrp id="#scipio">Scipio</personGrp> and Varus, for in consequence of their disagreement and disunion they were secretly trying to win the favour of <persName id="#juba">Juba</persName>, who was intolerable for the arrogance of his temper and his haughtiness by reason of his wealth and power.
