And he urged them to deliberate about themselves, and that he would not find fault with their deciding either way, and if they should be disposed to turn to the fortunate side, he should attribute the change to necessity; but if they preferred to oppose the danger and to undertake the hazard in defence of liberty, he should not only commend them, but admire their virtue, and make himself their commander and fellow-combatant, till they had tried the last fortune of their country, which was not <personGrp id="#utica">Utica</personGrp> or Adrumetum only, but <personGrp id="#rome">Rome</personGrp>, that had often by her might recovered from greater falls.
